An Act relative to school bus stop safety.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 265 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition, is hereby
2 amended by inserting after section 47, the following new section:
3 “Section 47A. A sex offender who has been finally classified as a level 2 or level 3 sex
4 offender, and for as long as the sex offender is obligated to register, shall be prohibited from
5 loitering within 500 feet of a school bus stop which has been designated as such by any city,
6 town, or school district.
7 For the purposes of this section, loitering shall mean remaining in the prohibited location
8 for more than 15 minutes. A sex offender who is the parent or legal guardian of a child scheduled
1 of 2

9 to depart from or arrive at a school bus stop, may remain at the prohibited location more than 15
10 minutes, but only until such time as the child has departed or arrived.
11 A sex offender who violates this section shall be punished by a fine of $500 for a first
12 offense; for a second offense by a fine of $1,000, or by imprisonment in a house of correction for
13 not more than 3 months, or by both such fine and imprisonment; and for a third or subsequent
14 offense by a fine of $1,500 and not less than 3 months nor more than 2 ½ years in a house of
15 correction. Written notification shall be made to the sex offender registry board of any such
16 violation.”
